text: The liver-colored moray (Gymnothorax hepaticus) is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian Oceans.Gymnothorax hepaticus at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Eduard Rüppell in 1830.Common names for Gymnothorax hepaticus at www.fishbase.org. ==References== hepaticus Category:Fish described in 1830
